rComments: Neuroscience is tough no matter what. Not only is this professor monotone, she never smiles, her feedback is not clear, and her study guides are not helpful what so ever. Too much information is given at a time and you are expected to know every minute detail as if this is your profession and not a second year class. Avoid this professor!!!
the class is very boring, and she is very boring also.  her tests are really tricky. prepare to fall asleep in class
It is clear that she loves neuroscience. Her exams are fair. You will do well if you go to class!

Dr. Ledoux is a nice professor, and a good one. The subject matter is heavy it's a bio course  so you have to put the effort in to do well. A lot of memorization of functions and parts. I think people who commented earlier were a little harsh. She's an upper year university professor so if you are expecting hand holding, yes, you will get attitude.

Dr. Ledoux was great and very passionate about the topic. She has a great background knowledge and shared from her own research which made the class more interesting. Very specific and clear on what she wants from and ensures no surprises on the midterms and final.  So cute! Really wanted people to love neuro. ... and she succeeded!

She is clear about what you need to know for the exams, which were totally reasonable, and is available to clarify any issues you may have with the material. She does speak really quickly so I wouldnt bother taking notes by hand. Dont expect her to just give you an A, but if you study hard you'll do well. She is also pretty funny from time to time.

She stated right off the bat that she was coming back after a break from teaching and that she is aware her students were not pleased with the difficulty of the course. She said she will take a different approach this time and I believe this was accomplished. She is a good professor in her current form and it is possible to do well in this course.

She has definitely changed her teaching style because her class is a lot more enjoyable now. She does go through the material pretty fast, but sometimes she basically gives you the answer she wants to see on the midterm, so you should go to class. Study the slides and you'll get an A.

Clearly since her first reviews on this site, Dr. Ledoux has become a more reasonable test-writer. Her midterms were fair and her lecture clarity improved as the semester went on. She tends to go quite fast, I would not recommend hand writing notes in her class. She doesn't require the text, but I would highly recommend it.

The professor explained at the beginning of the course that in the past there had been terrible marks and she realized this. She realized this was mostly art students and changed her tests to follow this. Read the textbook and prepare thoroughly for tests to do well ... and you will!
If you attend class she gives good hints of what to expect for midterms.

J'avais tellement hâte de prendre le cours de neuroscience. Finalement, ça a été un des pires cours de mon Bac. La professeure était désorganisé, son enseignement était incompréhensible. Selon son attitude, elle doit détester enseigner. Je comprends que c'était son premier cours en tant qu'enseignante et j'espère qu'elle s'améliorera.

There's not much to say other than she is the worst prof I've ever had. Horrible accent, little to no review, jams as much info in your head as she can, has an attitude, unhelpful, unclear with exam format, exams are difficult. Was forced to retake the course to not have my CGPA destroyed. What could be better?

Overall, this prof was very harsh. She relied heavily on the textbook. She did not explain the concepts well but expected you to know them right down to the very fine details. She was not eager to help me, but rather discouraged me when I went to seek help. The midterms and exams were definitely hard. Avoid this prof if you want good grades.

Everything in her lectures is from the book. I studied my butt off for the exams and found them to be pretty hard. Her lectures aren't as bad as people are saying but I did find her sort of rude. Textbook is a must. Don't go to class because she literally reads the book from her slides.

AVOID!!! If you can get another professor for this any class, ANY, that would save your GPA. This class ruined mine. Worked my ass off for the midterms and final and still only pulled off a C+ Way too hard, confusing, and literally everything is just straight from the book including her slides. She's not a bad person, just not a good teacher.

Extremely unclear with explanations and taught directly from the textbook, text book is extremely important as she expects you to know processes, yet doesn't explain them clearly in class. Midterms are hard and very specific.

You NEED the textbook for this class. She teaches right out of the book. She is very unclear, mispronounces a lot of words and uses french words sometimes, in the English class. The midterms are difficult and you really have to learn your stuff to pass.
Very confusing. Half the words she says are French which is annoying. Doesn't seem to know what she's talking about and gets lost easily.
Terrible! I'm sure she's very nice but she's extremely unclear, confusing and she keeps asking questions but disregards all answers unless they are her exact words.
It was her first class, so she was disorganize and not very confident. The subject was interesting, but she taugh it a way it wasn't interesting anymore...
